welcome.feature.refactoring.suggestions.title=Suggest refactorings

welcome.feature.refactoring.suggestions.steps=\
  Select a code fragment and right-click to open the context menu.\
  <p>\
  Select <b>AI Actions</b> and then <b>Suggest Refactoring</b>.\
  <p>\
  In the field with the refactored code, click <b>Show Diff</b> to open the diff viewer.
welcome.feature.refactoring.suggestions.afterSteps=\
  <b>Tip:</b> You can use this and other <b>AI Actions</b> without selecting a specific code fragment. \
  Place the caret in the desired class or method, choose the AI action, and select the required code fragment.

welcome.feature.explain.code.title=Explain code
welcome.feature.explain.code.steps=\
  Select a code fragment and right-click to open the context menu.\
  <p>\
  Select <b>AI Actions</b> and then <b>Explain Code</b>.
welcome.feature.explain.code.afterSteps=\
  This also works for regular expressions, SQL queries, cron expressions, and other injected fragments.

welcome.feature.inline.code.completion.title=Complete code
welcome.feature.inline.code.completion.steps=\
  Start typing in the editor to get instant suggestions.\
  <p>\
  To accept the suggested code, press <shortcut actionId="InsertInlineCompletionAction"/>.\
  <p>\
  To reject the suggestion, press <kbd>Esc</kbd>.
welcome.feature.inline.code.completion.after.steps=\
  You can also invoke code completion manually by pressing <shortcut actionId="CallInlineCompletionAction"/>.<p>\
  <b>Tip:</b> Hover over the code suggestion to change the key that accepts {0}'s suggestions.

welcome.feature.write.documentation.title=Generate documentation
welcome.feature.write.documentation.steps=\
  Select a code fragment and right-click to open the context menu.\
  <p>\
  Select <b>AI Actions</b> and then <b>Write Documentation</b>.
welcome.feature.write.documentation.after.steps=\
  <b>Prompt customization:</b><br>\
  Go to <b>Settings | Tools | {0} | Prompt Library | Write Documentation</b>.

welcome.feature.generate.commit.messages.title=Generate commit messages
welcome.feature.generate.commit.messages.before.steps=If you have changes:
welcome.feature.generate.commit.messages.steps=\
  Open the <icon src="com.intellij.icons.AllIcons.Actions.Commit"/> <b>Commit tool window</b>.\
  <p>\
  Click <icon src="com.intellij.llmInstaller.common.branding.LLMInstallerAIAssistantBrandingIcons.Logo16"/> <b>Generate Commit Message with {0}</b>.
welcome.feature.generate.commit.messages.after.steps=\
  <b>Prompt customization:</b><br>\
  Open the commit settings at the bottom-right corner of the commit message field.\
  <p>\
  Alternatively, go to <b>Settings | Tools | {0} | Prompt Library | Commit Message Generation</b>.

welcome.feature.code.generation.title=Generate code from descriptions

welcome.feature.code.generation.steps=\
  Place the caret anywhere in the editor or select a code fragment and press {0}.\
  <p>\
  In the input field, write your prompt and press <kbd>Enter</kbd>.\
  <p>\
  To improve results, write your follow-up prompt in the input field and press <kbd>Enter</kbd>.\
  <p>\
  Accept the generated code by pressing <shortcut actionId="ViewSource"/> or reject it by pressing <kbd>Esc</kbd>.

welcome.feature.name.suggestions.title=Suggest names

welcome.feature.name.suggestions.steps=\
  Place the caret on what you want to rename.\
  <p>\
  Right-click to open the context menu, select <b>Refactor</b> and then <b>Rename</b>.

welcome.feature.unit.tests.generation.title=Generate tests
welcome.feature.unit.tests.generation.steps=\
  Place the caret anywhere within a method and right-click to open the context menu.\
  <br>\
  Alternatively, press <shortcut actionId="ShowIntentionActions"/>.\
  <p>\
  Select <b>AI Actions</b> and then <b>Generate Unit Tests</b>.\
  <p>\
  To improve the generated code, click <b>Specify</b> and add new requirements in the <b>AI Diff</b> tab.
welcome.feature.unit.tests.generation.afterSteps=\
  <b>Prompt customization:</b><br>\
  Go to <b>Settings | Tools | {0} | Prompt Library | Generate Unit Tests</b>.

welcome.feature.convert.to.another.language.title=Convert to another language
welcome.feature.convert.to.another.language.steps=\
  Open a file you want to convert, place the caret in the editor and right-click to open the context menu.\
  <p>\
  Select <b>AI Actions</b> and then <b>Convert File to Another Language</b>.\
  <p>\
  Select the language you want to convert the current file to.


welcome.feature.ask.questions.title=Ask programming questions
welcome.feature.ask.questions.before.steps=\
  You can ask {0} general programming questions.<br><br>\
  <b>Prompt examples:</b>\
<ul>\
  <li>What's the CAP theorem?\
  <li>How do I validate an email address using regex?\
  <li>How do I generate random integers within a specific range in Java?\
  <li>Explain how to write an efficient Docker file for deploying Spring Boot applications.\
  <li>Provide step-by-step instructions on how to create a CRUD application using Ktor with RESTful API.\
</ul>

welcome.feature.reference.files.title=Reference files
welcome.feature.reference.files.before.steps=\
  Perform targeted queries within your project.<br><br>\
<b>Prompt examples:</b>\
<ul>\
  <li>Where in <b>#thisFile</b> is an off-by-one error?\
  <li>Which of my <b>#localChanges</b> has introduced an off-by-one error?\
  <li>Where in <b>#file:Foo.kt</b> is an off-by-one error?\
  <li>Where in <b>#symbol:Foo</b> is an off-by-one error?\
  <li>What value does <b>#jupyter_var:foo</b> have?\
</ul>


welcome.feature.ask.about.code.title=Ask about project code
welcome.feature.ask.about.code.steps=\
  Select a specific code fragment in the editor and right-click to open the context menu.\
  <p>\
  Select <b>AI Actions</b> and then <b>New Chat Using Selection</b>.
welcome.feature.ask.about.code.after.steps=\
  <b>Tip:</b> {0} is aware of the caret position and selected code in the editor, current file, and opened tabs.<br><br>\
  <b>Prompt examples:</b>\
<ul>\
  <li>What does <b>secretMethod</b> do?\
  <li>Where can I find <b>authorization</b> in my project?\
  <li>Explain the code at the caret.\
  <li>What does the selected code do?\
  <li>Describe the code in my current file.\
  <li>What files are open?\
</ul>

welcome.feature.ask.about.local.changes.and.commits.title=Ask about VCS
welcome.feature.ask.about.local.changes.and.commits.beforeSteps=You can ask {0} VCS-related questions.<p>\
  <b>Prompt examples:</b>\
  <ul>\
  <li>What was the last commit?\
  <li>Show me the commit history.\
  <li>Show me the difference between the last two commits.\
  <li>Show me the uncommitted changes.\
  <li>What are the outgoing changes?\
  </ul>

welcome.feature.craft.prompt.library.title=Create prompt library
welcome.feature.craft.prompt.library.before.steps=\
To create your own prompts, you can:\
<ul>\
  <li>Right-click in the editor to open the context menu and then go to <b>AI Actions | Add Your Prompts</b>.\
  <li>Click <icon src="com.intellij.icons.AllIcons.Actions.MenuSaveall"/> <b>Save Current Prompt</b> in the {0} chat input field to save your prompt.\
  <li>Or open the settings and then select <b>Tools | {0} | Prompt Library</b>.\
  </ul>\
<br>\
<b>Tip:</b> Use the <b>$SELECTION</b> variable to add the current code selection to the prompt.

welcome.feature.explain.commit.title=Explain commits
welcome.feature.explain.commit.steps=\
  Open <icon src="com.intellij.icons.AllIcons.General.Vcs"/> <b>Git tool window</b>.\
  <p>\
  In the commits pane, select one or more commits for {0} to explain.\
  <p>\
  Right-click and select <b>Explain Commit with {0}</b> in the context menu.

welcome.feature.find.potential.problems.title=Find errors and suggest fixes
welcome.feature.find.potential.problems.steps=\
  Select a code fragment and right-click to open the context menu.\
  <p>\
  Select <b>AI Actions</b> and then <b>Find Problems</b>.

welcome.feature.explain.runtime.error.title=Explain runtime errors
welcome.feature.explain.runtime.errors.before.steps=If you have a runtime error:
welcome.feature.explain.runtime.errors.steps=\
  Click <icon src="com.intellij.llmInstaller.common.branding.LLMInstallerAIAssistantBrandingIcons.Logo16"/> <b>Explain with AI</b> in the console.\
  <p>\
  Alternatively, select the error message, open the context menu, and click <b>Explain error message with AI</b>.

