welcome.feature.sql.generate.by.nl.request.title=Generate SQL queries based on natural language requests
welcome.feature.sql.generate.by.nl.request.steps=\
  Place the caret anywhere in the editor or select a code fragment and press <shortcut actionId="AIAssistant.Editor.ForceGenerateCodeInEditor"/>.\
  <p>\
  In the input field, write your prompt for the query and press <kbd>Enter</kbd>.\
  <p>\
  To fine-tune the results, write a follow-up prompt in the input field and press <kbd>Enter</kbd>.\
  <p>\
  Accept the generated query by pressing {0} or reject it by pressing <kbd>Esc</kbd>.

welcome.feature.sql.attach.schema.title=Attach a schema to improve interaction
welcome.feature.sql.attach.schema.before.steps=You can enhance the quality of generated SQL queries by providing the context of the database schema you are working with.
welcome.feature.sql.attach.schema.steps=\
  Open the AI chat.\
  <p>\
  Attach the schema with the help of the drop-down list.\
  <p>\
  {0} will get access to the structure of the attached schema, providing information about it to the LLM.\
  <p>\
  Start chatting.

welcome.feature.sql.ask.insights.title=Ask for insights about your database
welcome.feature.sql.ask.insights.before.steps=\
  Since the {0} chat is aware of your schema, you can ask questions about your database objects.\
  Prompt examples:\
  <ul>\
    <li><i>Which tables contain columns with the BLOB type?</i>\
    <li><i>What tables is <code>film_actor</code> connected to via foreign keys?</i>\
    <li><i>Which tables are partitioned?</i>\
    <li><i>Which tables have no primary keys?</i>\
  </ul>

welcome.feature.sql.optimize.query.title=Request query optimization
welcome.feature.sql.optimize.query.before.steps=You can send a query to the AI chat along with the result of using <i>Explain Plan</i> on the query, and {0} will offer you possible optimizations.
welcome.feature.sql.optimize.query.steps=\
  Attach the schema to the chat \u2013 the context will help {0} optimize your query.\
  <p>\
  Craft a prompt with a request for optimization, including the query, the <i>Explain Plan</i> result, and the request.\
  <p>\
  Paste the suggested refactoring and test it.

welcome.feature.sql.explain.queries.title=Explain queries
welcome.feature.sql.explain.queries.steps=\
  Put the caret on a query and right-click to open the context menu.\
  <p>\
  Select <i>AI Actions</i> and then <i>Explain Code</i>.
welcome.feature.sql.explain.queries.after.steps=<b>Tip</b>: This also works for regular expressions, Python snippets, and other code fragments.

welcome.feature.sql.create.prompt.library.title=Create a prompt library
welcome.feature.sql.create.prompt.library.steps=\
  Right-click in the editor to open the context menu and then go to <i>AI Actions</i> | <i>Add Your Prompts</i>.\
  <p>\
  Click <i>Save Current Prompt</i> in the {0} chat input field to save your prompt.\
  <p>\
  Alternatively, open the settings and then select <i>Tools</i> | <i>{0}</i> | <i>Prompt Library</i>.
welcome.feature.sql.create.prompt.library.after.steps=\
  <b>Tip</b>: You can use the <code>$SELECTION$</code> variable to add the current code selection to the prompt.\
  <br/><br/>Prompt examples:\
  <ul>\
    <li><i>Convert this SQL to the PostgreSQL dialect.</i>\
    <li><i>Write Python code that duplicates the functionality of this query.</i>\
    <li><i>Refactor this SQL: replace subquery with CTE.</i>\
    <li><i>Add aliases to all tables in this query.</i>\
  </ul>

welcome.feature.sql.correct.syntax.title=Correct your SQL syntax
welcome.feature.sql.correct.syntax.steps=\
  Put the caret on the syntax error in your SQL code.\
  <p>\
  Select <i>AI Actions</i> and then <i>Fix SQL Problem</i>.\
  <p>\
  The code will be corrected in the editor.\
  <p>\
  Use the <i>Undo</i> action if you are not satisfied with the result.

welcome.feature.sql.use.correct.objects.title=Request to use the correct database objects
welcome.feature.sql.use.correct.objects.before.steps={0} perfectly handles misusages of database objects. Knowing the database schema, it can detect which object you were supposed to use.
welcome.feature.sql.use.correct.objects.steps=\
  Put the caret on the syntax error in your SQL code.\
  <p>\
  Select <i>AI Actions</i> and then <i>Fix SQL Problem</i>.\
  <p>\
  The code will be corrected in the editor.\
  <p>\
  Use the <i>Undo</i> action if you are not satisfied with the result.

